Quick setup - if you've done git repository before

- Creating a new repository on the commandline
  echo "$ git beginner-guide repo" >> README.md
  
  git init
  git add <YOUR FILE NAME>
  git commit -m "first commit"
  git remote add origin https://github.com/myaccount-name-here/git-beginner-guide-repo-git
  git push -u origin master


- Pushing to an existing repository from commandline
  
  git remote add origin https://github.com/myaccount-name-here/git-beginner-guide-repo-git
  git push -u origin master
  git status
  

- To clone to your local computer
   git clone [https Address]

- To move into repository on your computer
   cd [Name of the repository]
   
- Useful commands for Git
   git log  -> get the log history
   git chechout  -> revert back all your changes since the last committed
   git checkout [FILE NAME]
   git diff [FILE NAME]  -> check the differences in the changes committed
   git clean -dfx
   

